Lindelwa Jabavu has been appointed to head the organisation until the process to employ a new CEO is finalised. JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Joe Maswanganyi has appointed an acting CEO for the Road Accident Fund.Lindelwa Jabavu has been appointed to head the organisation until the process to employ a new CEO is finalised.The minister says that Jabavu has extensive experience and her appointment will guarantee that stability is maintained during the ushering in of a new compensation system under the Road Accident Benefit Scheme.More to follow.